a simple example of a Library Management System using Visual Basic (VB). This project allows users to manage books, patrons, and borrowing transactions.

Objective:
Develop a Library Management System using Visual Basic to manage and organize books, patrons, and borrowing transactions in a library setting.

Outcome:
A user-friendly application that enables library staff to perform tasks such as adding new books, adding new patrons, tracking borrowed books, and returning books.

Technologies Used:
Language: Visual Basic (VB)
User Interface: Windows Forms Application
Database: In this example, a simple in-memory data structure (List) is used for storing data. For a real-world scenario, you might use a database like Microsoft Access or SQL Server.
